<HEADLINE>
TAKING TAXI MOST WORRISOME PERSONAL SAFETY ISSUE: POLL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 8 (CNA) 03/08/07  21:39:12 (By Deborah Kuo)
</P>
<P>
Taking a taxi, particularly at night, is the most worrisome
matter for women in Taiwan in terms of personal safety, results
of a poll showed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the private activist group Modern Women's
Foundation Feb. 26-March 5, found that taking a taxi could be the
most "horrifying" experience for Taiwanese women, with 83.2
percent expressing grave concern.
</P>
<P>
The taxi-scare phenomenon has topped all personal safety concerns
in the foundation's polls for three consecutive years, the
pollsters said.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 percent of the respondents said most personal safety
problems are associated with public places.
</P>
<P>
Other "horrifying" experiences included being spied on by hidden
cameras -- cited by 83% -- physical violence and sexual
harassment in public places, the poll found.
</P>
<P>
Over half of the respondents said date violence, domestic
violence, sexual discrimination and physical assault in the work
place are also worrisome issues.
</P>
<P>
The poll of female citizens aged 13 years and over, randomly
selected nationwide, was conducted online to mark Women's Day.
The results are based on 811 valid responses.
</P>
